Phumzile Sitole is the daughter of Mzansi’s famous chef and former magazine editor, Mama Dorah Sitole.  Phumzile has been working really hard to make a name for herself as an actress. So far she has worked on shows such as The Good Fight, Elementary and Orange Is the New Black where she is a regular actress known as Antoinetta ‘Akers’ Kerson. This Mzansi-born actress has a BA in Theatre and Performance at the University of Cape Town in the bag and also a Master of Fine Arts in Theatre at Columbia University in New York. 